mode-line-hack.el is a ModeLineConfiguration by JaeyounChung will let you hide the ModeLine whenever there is only one [[Window]] displayed in the [[Frame]].  Information like buffer name and TextCursor position ([[Point]]) is put in the HeaderLine instead.  This might be useful for vi refugees.

http://emacs.kldp.org/~jay/emacs/

To completely remove the modeline from one buffer (buffer-specific) evaluate:

{{{
    (setq mode-line-format nil)
}}}

and to make it affect all buffers evaluate:

{{{
    (setq-default mode-line-format nil) 
}}}

----
